<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="objectify_data"><objectify_data action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><condition/><fields/><key>total_incident_count</key><max_results/><number>OBD0001033</number><object display_value="sample_user_data">f884544c4fce5200e3d8a3618110c727</object><offset/><order>100</order><override_target>false</override_target><script><![CDATA[/*
Available variables:
input - JSON object containing all processed input data from the parent Object Definition

Result variable:
answer - Value or object to be included in the key for this Data Definition

Example:
var returnObject = {};
returnObject.myStaticField = 'Lemur';
returnObject.myInputField = input.[myKey];
returnObject.myDynamicField = gs.getUserID();
answer = returnObject;
*/

var count = new GlideAggregate('incident');
count.addAggregate('COUNT');
count.addQuery('caller_id', input.sys_id.toString());
count.query();
var incidents = 0;
if (count.next())
	incidents = count.getAggregate('COUNT');
answer = incidents;]]></script><secure_mode>true</secure_mode><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-04 01:25:07</sys_created_on><sys_id>5766944c4fce5200e3d8a3618110c77b</sys_id><sys_mod_count>11</sys_mod_count><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-27 17:17:18</sys_updated_on><table/><target/><target_table/><type>scripted</type><value/></objectify_data></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_57d5da774f7d5200e3d8a3618110c75b
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_label/><action_name/><action_query>false</action_query><action_run_at>server</action_run_at><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><application/><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>objectify_object</collection><condition>current.identifier.changes() || current.accepts_input.changes() || current.request_payload.changes()</condition><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition/><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Objectify - Generate code snippets</name><onclick/><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><read_access_action>false</read_access_action><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {
	//Gather identifier, acceptsInput, and input
	var identifier = current.getValue('identifier');
	var acceptsInput = current.getValue('accepts_input');
	var input = '';
	if (acceptsInput == true){
		try{
			input = new global.JSON().encode(eval(current.getValue('request_payload')));
		}
		catch(error){
			gs.info('Objectify: Error processing sample request payload for object "' + current.getValue('key') + '": ' + error);
		}
	}
	
	//Generate snippets
	current.angular = getAngularSnippet(identifier, acceptsInput, input);
	current.javascript = getJavascriptSnippet(identifier, acceptsInput, input);
	current.glide = getGlideSnippet(identifier, acceptsInput, input);
})(current, previous);

//Generate angular snippet
function getAngularSnippet(identifier, acceptsInput, input){
	var snippet = '';
	if (acceptsInput == true)
		snippet += "var input = " + input + ";\n";
	snippet += "$http.post('/api/snc/objectify/postobject?identifier=" + identifier + "'";
	if (acceptsInput == true)
		snippet += ", input";
	snippet+= ").success(function(response){\n\tconsole.log('Objectify results for " + identifier + ": ' + JSON.stringify(response));\n});\n";
	return snippet;
}

//Generate javascript snippet
function getJavascriptSnippet(identifier, acceptsInput, input){
	var snippet = '';
	snippet += "var input = ";
	if (acceptsInput == true)
		snippet += "'" + input + "'";
	else
		snippet += "''";
	snippet+= ";\nvar client=new XMLHttpRequest();\nclient.open('post','/api/snc/objectify/postobject?identifier=" + identifier + "');\nclient.setRequestHeader('Accept','application/json');\nclient.setRequestHeader('Content-Type','application/json');\nclient.onreadystatechange = function() {\n\tif (client.status === 200)\n\t\tconsole.log('Objectify results for " + identifier + ": ' + JSON.stringify(JSON.parse(client.response).result));\n};\nclient.send(input);\n";
	return snippet;
}

//Generate glide snippet
function getGlideSnippet(identifier, acceptsInput, input){
	var snippet = '';
	if (acceptsInput == true)
		snippet += "var input = " + input + ";\n";
	snippet += "var objectifyHelper = new global.objectify();\nvar response = objectifyHelper.postObject('" + identifier + "'";
	if (acceptsInput == true)
		snippet += ", input";
	snippet+= ");\n";
	return snippet;

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="objectify_data"><objectify_data action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><condition/><fields/><key>delete_record</key><max_results/><number>OBD0001051</number><object display_value="delete_record">b16709e113069200c794b7a12244b09f</object><offset/><order>100</order><override_target>false</override_target><script><![CDATA[/*
Available variables:
input - JSON object containing all processed input data from the parent Object Definition

Result variable:
answer - Value or object to be included in the key for this Data Definition

Example:
var returnObject = {};
returnObject.myStaticField = 'Lemur';
returnObject.myInputField = input.[myKey];
returnObject.myDynamicField = gs.getUserID();
answer = returnObject;
 */

var delRec = new GlideRecordSecure(input.table);
delRec.addQuery("sys_id", input.sys_id);
delRec.query();
if (delRec.next() && delRec.canDelete()){
	delRec.deleteRecord();
	answer = 'SUCCESS';
}
else
	answer = 'FAILURE';]]></script><secure_mode>true</secure_mode><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-09 01:01:11</sys_created_on><sys_id>2ec0062513469200c794b7a12244b08a</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-20 21:13:57</sys_updated_on><table/><target/><target_table/><type>scripted</type><value/></objectify_data></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="DELETE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.codeSearchUtils_ajax</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>codeSearchUtils_ajax</name><script><![CDATA[var codeSearchUtils_ajax = Class.create();
codeSearchUtils_ajax.prototype = {
	initialize: function() {
	},
	getSearchResults: function(){
		term = this.getParameter('term');
		searchType = this.getParameter('searchType');
		gs.log("CodeSearchUI: term"+term)
		gs.log("CodeSearchUI: queryType"+searchType)
		var delimiter = ",";
		if(searchType == "And")
			useAndQuery = true;
		else
			useAndQuery = false;
		
		var csu = new codeSearchUtils();
		var	instancePath= "https://" + gs.getProperty('instance_name') + ".service-now.com/";
		var searchResults = csu.searchForTerm(term.toString(), useAndQuery, false, delimiter,resultFormat);
		
		return searchResults;
		
	},
	type: 'codeSearchUtils_ajax'
};

]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-10-18 14:09:29</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>436cb0c3db31cb405dbe38f0ad961995</sys_id><sys_mod_count>2</sys_mod_count><sys_name>codeSearchUtils_ajax</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_436cb0c3db31cb405dbe38f0ad961995</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2017-10-18 14:26:14</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

For instance, would you like to detect GlideDateTime values in your output and automatically transform those into Unix time? Of course you would - in fact, that Data Transformer is included with Objectify.<ul><li><b>Name</b>: A descriptive name for this Data Transformer, so folks know what it's for.</li><li><b>Type</b>: How this Data Transformer is triggered, either via a field data type (Smart Key Definition fields only) or regex. Regex transformers traverse the entire output object searching for patterns and then transforming them - this can affect performance, if you aren't careful.</li><li><b>Data type</b>: (Data type only) Type of data to transform, by ServiceNow field type. This only works for fields selected on a Smart Key Definition.</li><li><b>Regex</b>: (Regex only) Regex against which to match data values.</li><li><b>Script</b>: Server-side script to generate and return the transformed value for this Data Transformer (see comments in script for details).</li></ul></text><type display_value="Info Box sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_label/><action_name/><action_query>false</action_query><action_run_at>server</action_run_at><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><application/><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>objectify_data_transformer</collection><condition>current.active == true</condition><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition/><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Objectify - Check for dupe transformer</name><onclick/><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><read_access_action>false</read_access_action><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {
	var dataTransformer = new GlideRecord("objectify_data_transformer");
	dataTransformer.addQuery("active", true);
	dataTransformer.addQuery("type", "data_type");
	dataTransformer.addQuery("data_type", current.data_type);
	dataTransformer.addQuery("sys_id", "!=", current.sys_id);
	dataTransformer.query();
	if (dataTransformer.next()) {
		gs.addErrorMessage('An active Data Transformer already exists for data type ' + current.data_type.getDisplayValue() + '. Aborting.');
		current.setAbortAction(true);
	}
})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-03 20:52:20</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>a8c71ffb4fbd5200e3d8a3618110c734</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Objectify - Check for dupe transformer</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_a8c71ffb4fbd5200e3d8a3618110c734</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-09 19:06:01</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: objectify_data_49f1c22513469200c794b7a12244b0d1
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="objectify_data"><objectify_data action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><condition/><fields/><key>insert_record</key><max_results/><number>OBD0001052</number><object display_value="insert_record">a3370de113069200c794b7a12244b0c4</object><offset/><order>100</order><override_target>false</override_target><script><![CDATA[/*
Available variables:
input - JSON object containing all processed input data from the parent Object Definition

Result variable:
answer - Value or object to be included in the key for this Data Definition

Example:
var returnObject = {};
returnObject.myStaticField = 'Lemur';
returnObject.myInputField = input.[myKey];
returnObject.myDynamicField = gs.getUserID();
answer = returnObject;
*/

var answer;
var newRec = new GlideRecordSecure(input.table);
if (newRec.canCreate()){
	newRec.initialize();
	for (var field in input.fields)
		newRec.setValue(field, input.fields[field]);
	newRec.insert();
	answer = {
		"sys_id":newRec.sys_id.toString(),
		"label":newRec.getDisplayValue()
	};
}]]></script><secure_mode>true</secure_mode><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-09 01:07:47</sys_created_on><sys_id>49f1c22513469200c794b7a12244b0d1</sys_id><sys_mod_count>2</sys_mod_count><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-20 21:13:57</sys_updated_on><table/><target/><target_table/><type>scripted</type><value/></objectify_data></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: objectify_magic_key_ea8ab2b34fbd5200e3d8a3618110c777
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="objectify_magic_key"><objectify_magic_key action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><keys>sys_id,table</keys><name>Record Fetcher</name><number>OBM0001006</number><script><![CDATA[/*
Available variables:
obj - JSON object that triggered this Magic Key - Access keys like obj.[myKey]

Result variable:
answer - Object to be concatenated to the object that triggered this Magic Key

Example:
var returnObject = {};
returnObject.additional_data = 'Transformed for ' + obj.myKey;
answer = returnObject;
*/

//Transform a table and a sys_id into a full GlideRecord
var returnObject;
var magicRec = new GlideRecord(obj.table);
if (magicRec.get(obj.sys_id))
	returnObject = magicRec;
answer = returnObject;]]></script><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-03 18:42:43</sys_created_on><sys_id>ea8ab2b34fbd5200e3d8a3618110c777</sys_id><sys_mod_count>19</sys_mod_count><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-06 17:38:01</sys_updated_on><type>input</type></objectify_magic_key></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_label/><action_name/><action_query>false</action_query><action_run_at>server</action_run_at><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><application/><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>objectify_object</collection><condition>current.active == true</condition><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition/><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Objectify - Check for duplicate objects</name><onclick/><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><read_access_action>false</read_access_action><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {
	var objRec = new GlideRecord("objectify_object");
	objRec.addQuery("active", true);
	objRec.addQuery("identifier", current.identifier);
	objRec.addQuery("sys_id", "!=", current.sys_id);
	objRec.query();
	if (objRec.next()) {
		gs.addErrorMessage('An active Object Definition already exists with identifier ' + current.identifier + '. Aborting.');
		current.setAbortAction(true);
	}
})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-02-29 15:10:36</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>4a9cea36137d1200c794b7a12244b0da</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Objectify - Check for duplicate objects</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_4a9cea36137d1200c794b7a12244b0da</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-03 23:30:20</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_script"><sys_ui_script action="DELETE"><active>true</active><description/><global>false</global><name>codeSearchUtil_ajaxHelper</name><script><![CDATA[angular.module('codeSearchUtil_ajaxHelper', []);
angular.module('codeSearchUtil_ajaxHelper').service('GlideAjax', function($rootScope) {
	var glideAjax = window.GlideAjax;
	glideAjax.prototype.getJSON = function(callback) {
		this.getXMLAnswer(function(answer) {
			var answerJSON = JSON.parse(answer);
			callback(answerJSON);
			$rootScope.$apply();
		});

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_label/><action_name/><action_query>false</action_query><action_run_at>server</action_run_at><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><application/><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>objectify_data</collection><condition>current.active == true</condition><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition/><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Objectify - Check for duplicate key</name><onclick/><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><read_access_action>false</read_access_action><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {
	var objDataRec = new GlideRecord("objectify_data");
	objDataRec.addQuery("active", true);
	objDataRec.addQuery("object", current.object.sys_id);
	objDataRec.addQuery("key", current.key);
	objDataRec.addQuery("sys_id", "!=", current.sys_id);
	objDataRec.query();
	if (objDataRec.next()) {
		gs.addErrorMessage('An active Key Definition already exists in Object Definition ' + current.object.getDisplayValue() + ' with key ' + current.key + '. Aborting.');
		current.setAbortAction(true);
	}
})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-02-29 15:38:20</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>739376f6137d1200c794b7a12244b0c3</sys_id><sys_mod_count>5</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Objectify - Check for duplicate key</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_739376f6137d1200c794b7a12244b0c3</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-03 23:31:43</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="objectify_data_transformer"><objectify_data_transformer action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>false</active><data_type display_value="Translated Text">e62dabc1bf3320001875647fcf073967</data_type><name>Translated Text (from English)</name><number>OBD0001022</number><regex/><script><![CDATA[/*
Available variables:
value - Original system value
element - GlideElement of original field (Data Type only)

Result variable:
answer - Transformed value

Example:
answer = 'Transformed ' + value;
*/

var tableName = element.getTableName();
var fieldName = element.getED().toString();
var sysID = element.getGlideRecord().sys_id.toString();
var userLanguage = gs.getUser().getLanguage();

var translatedTextRec = new GlideRecord('sys_translated_text');
translatedTextRec.addQuery("tablename", tableName);
translatedTextRec.addQuery("fieldname", fieldName);
translatedTextRec.addQuery("language", userLanguage);
translatedTextRec.addQuery("documentkey", sysID);
translatedTextRec.query();
if (translatedTextRec.next())
	answer = translatedTextRec.getValue('value');
else
	answer = value;]]></script><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-04-23 15:20:13</sys_created_on><sys_id>6254749c13cb5600c794b7a12244b019</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-04-23 15:20:13</sys_updated_on><type>data_type</type></objectify_data_transformer></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload: Objectifysys_properties_categoryben.hollifield@snc_SHARE2016-02-29 15:15:52true436e6a76137d1200c794b7a12244b01310Objectifyglobalfalseglobalsys_properties_category_436e6a76137d1200c794b7a12244b013ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE2016-03-08 20:57:14<![CDATA[<p><strong>Objectify Details</strong></p> <p>Objectify is the magical data gathering* engine that wants you to spend less time finding data and more time creating amazing user experiences.</p> <p>With Objectify, building and consuming data is easy. Configure and test your JSON Object & Key Definitions with simple forms and condition builders (don't worry, we let you script if you really want to). Then, consume the data via a pre-built REST API and auto-generated snippets that you can drop directly into your code.</p> <p>Features:</p> <ul> <li>Choose from 3 types of Object Definitions, each offering a unique level of simplicity and capability: <ul> <li>Simple - Add static or simple dynamic key:value pairs to your Object.</li> <li>Smart - Use a sophisticated conditions-based engine to add arrays of dynamic data to your Object.</li> <li>Scripted - Do whatever you like!</li> </ul> </li> <li>Include input when invoking an Object Definition - use that input to make data gathering as dynamic and context-aware as you like.</li> <li>Use customizable Magic Keys to transform simple input/output key values into complex data structures.</li> <li>Use customizable Data Transformers to translate output data into formats perfect for your needs.</li> <li>Use sample input and sample output directly on the configuration form to test your Object as you build.</li> <li>Cut & paste auto-generated snippets directly into your code to consume the Objects you build.</li> </ul> <p><em>*Hey - Did you know that you can also use Objectify to perform actions on the server? Check out the sample insert/update/delete record Object Definitions for examples.</em></p> <p><strong>Objectify Properties</strong></p>]]>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ws_operation"><sys_ws_operation action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><consumes>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</consumes><consumes_customized>false</consumes_customized><default_operation_uri/><enforce_acl/><http_method>POST</http_method><name>postObject</name><operation_script><![CDATA[(function process(/*RESTAPIRequest*/ request, /*RESTAPIResponse*/ response) {
	var identifier = String(request.queryParams.identifier);
	var input = request.body.data;
	
	//Process Object Definition
	var objectifyHelper = new global.objectify();
	var postObjectReturn = objectifyHelper.postObject(identifier, input);
	
	//Check for erroneous Object processing
	if ('objectify_error' in postObjectReturn && 'objectify_error_code' in postObjectReturn){
		var objectifyError = new sn_ws_err.ServiceError();
		objectifyError.setStatus(postObjectReturn.objectify_error_code);
		objectifyError.setMessage('Objectify Error');
		objectifyError.setDetail(postObjectReturn.objectify_error);
		postObjectReturn = objectifyError;
	}
	
	return postObjectReturn;
})(request, response);]]></operation_script><operation_uri>/api/snc/objectify/postobject</operation_uri><produces>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</produces><produces_customized>false</produces_customized><relative_path>/postobject</relative_path><request_example>{"myKey":"myValue"}</request_example><requires_acl_authorization>false</requires_acl_authorization><requires_authentication>false</requires_authentication><short_description>Given an Object Definition identifier and optional input, return output object</short_description><sys_class_name>sys_ws_operation</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-03 14:41:22</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>f5e24ebf4f3d5200e3d8a3618110c701</sys_id><sys_mod_count>24</sys_mod_count><sys_name>postObject</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ws_operation_f5e24ebf4f3d5200e3d8a3618110c701</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-05-27 12:27:49</sys_updated_on><web_service_definition display_value="Objectify">7034faf6137d1200c794b7a12244b03a</web_service_definition><web_service_version/></sys_ws_operation></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload: <record_update><sys_ui_section caption="" section_id="b54a3e734fbd5200e3d8a3618110c760" sys_domain="global" table="objectify_magic_key" version="3" view=""><sys_ui_annotation action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><is_plain_text>false</is_plain_text><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-06 17:48:09</sys_created_on><sys_id>08ea82b8130a5200c794b7a12244b025</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-06 17:48:09</sys_updated_on><text>Magic Keys recognize a key or set of keys in your input/output object and transform it into a richer data set that you can use in Key Definitions or your application. For instance, would you like to detect keys of <i>table</i> and <i>sys_id</i> in your input object and automatically transform that into a full GlideRecord object? Of course you would - in fact, that Magic Key is included with Objectify.<ul><li><b>Name</b>: A descriptive name for this Magic Key, so folks know what it's for.</li><li><b>Type</b>: Where to apply the Magic Key, whether to the input (request) object or the output (response) object.</li><li><b>Keys</b>: Comma-separated list of keys to look for in the object. <i>All</i> of these keys must be found at the <i>same level</i> of the object hierarchy in order for the Magic Key to trigger.</li><li><b>Script</b>: Server-side script to generate and return the value for this Magic Key. Return value <i>must</i> be an object, and it will be concatenated with the original object that triggered this Magic Key (see comments in script for details).</li></ul></text><type sys_update_xml.payload: <record_update><sys_ui_section caption="" section_id="63137eb6137d1200c794b7a12244b0f2" sys_domain="global" table="objectify_data" version="3" view=""><sys_ui_annotation action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><is_plain_text>false</is_plain_text><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-20 21:19:49</sys_created_on><sys_id>c991031d13169600c794b7a12244b0c9</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-20 21:19:49</sys_updated_on><text>A Key Definition represents a data gathering job. The results of this job will comprise a portion of the grand JSON package produced for the parent Object Definition.<ul><li><b>Key</b>: A unique identifier - This is the key you will use to access this value in the final JSON object.</li><li><b>Type</b>: The type of Key Definition, whether Simple, Smart, or Scripted. Choose wisely.</li><li><b>Object definition</b>: The parent Object Definition to which this Key Definition is subservient.</li><li><b>Value</b>: (Simple only) The value for this key. (Here's a secret - you can prepend the value with <i>javascript:</i> to utilize dynamic data or access your input data.)</li><li><b>Order</b>: (Scripted only) The order in which this Key Definition will run, relative to other Key Definitions - only useful when processing data.</li><li><b>Script</b>: (Scripted only) Server-side script to generate and return the value for this key (see comments in script for details).</li><li><b>Table</b>: (Smart only) The table against which you wish to query.</li><li><b>Max results</b>: (Smart only) The maximum number of query results to return. Leave blank for all results, you glutton. (You can access input data here like <i>javascript:input.[max_results]</i>)</li><li><b>Offset</b>: (Smart only) An offset to apply to the query results (ie - give me results staring at the 10th result) - great for pagination! Leave blank for no offset. (You can access input data here like <i>javascript:input.[offset]</i>)</li><li><b>Condition</b>: (Smart only) The conditions to apply to the query. Don't forget, you can use terms like <i>javascript:gs.getUserID()</i> or <i>javascript:input.[myKey]</i> to utilize dynamic data or access your input data. Some options are limited when using a GlideRecord in your input object - you cannot access values directly - try using <i>input.myRec.[field].toString()</i></li><li><b>Secure mode</b>: (Smart only) Do you wish to use GlideRecordSecure or just plain GlideRecord for the queries? Yeah, you're right - safety first.</li></ul></text><type display_value="Info Box Blue">753f88a80f930000b12e6903cfe01206</type></sys_ui_annotation><sys_ui_element <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_label/><action_name/><action_query>false</action_query><action_run_at>server</action_run_at><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><application/><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>objectify_additional_data</collection><condition>current.active == true</condition><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition/><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Objectify - Check for duplicate add data</name><onclick/><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><read_access_action>false</read_access_action><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {
	var addDataRec = new GlideRecord("objectify_additional_data");
	addDataRec.addQuery("active", true);
	addDataRec.addQuery("object_data", current.object_data.sys_id);
	addDataRec.addQuery("key", current.key);
	addDataRec.addQuery("sys_id", "!=", current.sys_id);
	addDataRec.query();
	if (addDataRec.next()) {
		gs.addErrorMessage('An active Additional Data already exists in Key Definition ' + current.object_data.getDisplayValue() + ' with key ' + current.key + '. Aborting.');
		current.setAbortAction(true);
	}
})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-03 23:37:35</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_id>63bd33f74ffd5200e3d8a3618110c790</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Objectify - Check for duplicate add data</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_63bd33f74ffd5200e3d8a3618110c790</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-03 23:37:35</sys_updated_on><template/><when>before</when></sys_script></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="objectify_data"><objectify_data action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><condition/><fields/><key>fetchCode_api</key><max_results/><number>OBD0001001</number><object display_value="Code_Search">b81a99c7db71cb405dbe38f0ad961948</object><offset/><order>100</order><override_target>false</override_target><script><![CDATA[/*
Available variables:
input - JSON object containing all processed input data from the parent Object Definition

Result variable:
answer - Value or object to be included in the key for this Data Definition

Example:
var returnObject = {
	
};
returnObject.myStaticField = 'Lemur';
returnObject.myInputField = input.[myKey];
returnObject.myDynamicField = gs.getUserID();
answer = returnObject;
 */

var term = input.term;
var searchType = input.searchType;
var additionalFilter = input.additionalFilter;

var delimiter = ",";
if(searchType == "And")
	useAndQuery = true;
else
	useAndQuery = false;

var csu = new fetchCodeUtils();
var searchResults = csu.searchForTerm(term.toString(), useAndQuery, false, delimiter,additionalFilter);

answer = JSON.parse(searchResults);
]]></script><secure_mode>true</secure_mode><sys_created_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-10-18 16:24:58</sys_created_on><sys_id>3d9a5dc7db71cb405dbe38f0ad961916</sys_id><sys_mod_count>10</sys_mod_count><sys_updated_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2017-10-20 13:31:05</sys_updated_on><table/><target/><target_table/><type>scripted</type><value/></objectify_data></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: objectify_data_b9c3862513469200c794b7a12244b0b5
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="objectify_data"><objectify_data action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><condition/><fields/><key>update_record</key><max_results/><number>OBD0001053</number><object display_value="update_record">54674de113069200c794b7a12244b04a</object><offset/><order>100</order><override_target>false</override_target><script><![CDATA[/*
Available variables:
input - JSON object containing all processed input data from the parent Object Definition

Result variable:
answer - Value or object to be included in the key for this Data Definition

Example:
var returnObject = {};
returnObject.myStaticField = 'Lemur';
returnObject.myInputField = input.[myKey];
returnObject.myDynamicField = gs.getUserID();
answer = returnObject;
*/

var answer;
var newRec = new GlideRecordSecure(input.table);
newRec.addQuery("sys_id", input.sys_id);
newRec.query();
if (newRec.next() && newRec.canWrite()){
	for (var field in input.fields)
		newRec.setValue(field, input.fields[field]);
	newRec.update();
	answer = {
		"sys_id":newRec.sys_id.toString(),
		"label":newRec.getDisplayValue()
	};
}]]></script><secure_mode>true</secure_mode><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-09 01:13:47</sys_created_on><sys_id>b9c3862513469200c794b7a12244b0b5</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-03-20 21:13:57</sys_updated_on><table/><target/><target_table/><type>scripted</type><value/></objectify_data></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_script"><sys_ui_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><description/><global>false</global><name>fc_functions</name><script><![CDATA[angular.module('FetchCode', [])
    .controller('searchUtils', ['$location', '$scope', '$http', function($location, $scope, $http) {
        $scope.formats = ["Records", "Lists", "Both"];
        $scope.searchTypes = ["And", "Or"];
        $scope.searchResults = "";
        $scope.instancePath = $location.absUrl().split('code_search_util')[0];
        $scope.additionalFilter = ""
        $scope.searchTerm = ""
        
        $scope.performSearch = function() {

            var pathObj = {};
            pathObj.searchTerm = $scope.searchTerm;
            pathObj.searchType = $scope.searchType;
            pathObj.additionalFilter = $scope.additionalFilter;

            $location.path('/' + JSON.stringify(pathObj));

        };
        $scope.clearSearch = function() {

            $location.path();

        };

        $scope.$on('$locationChangeSuccess', function(event) {
            try {
                $scope.gettingData = true;
                console.log("locationChangeSuccess")
                var vars = $location.path();
				console.log("vars: "+vars)
                var searchParams = JSON.parse(vars.replace('/', '').toString());

                if (searchParams.searchTerm && searchParams.searchTerm != 'undefined')
                    $scope.searchTerm = searchParams.searchTerm;

                if (searchParams.searchType && searchParams.searchType != 'undefined')
                    $scope.searchType = searchParams.searchType;

                if (searchParams.additionalFilter && searchParams.additionalFilter != 'undefined')
                    $scope.additionalFilter = searchParams.additionalFilter;
                else
                    searchParams.additionalFilter = "null=NULL";

                var input = { "searchType": searchParams.searchType, "term": searchParams.searchTerm, "additionalFilter": searchParams.additionalFilter };
                if (input.term) {
                    $http.post('/api/snc/objectify/postobject?identifier=FetchCode', input).then(function(response) {
                        if (response.data.result.error) {
                            $scope.searchResults = response.data.result.error;
                            $scope.responseStatus = 'error';
                        } else {
                            $scope.searchResults = response.data.result.fetchCode_api;
                            $scope.responseStatus = 'success';
                        }
						var responseObj = response.data.result.fetchCode_api;
                        console.log(responseObj);
                        // console.log($scope)

                    }).finally(function() {
                        $scope.gettingData = false;
                    });
                } else {
                    $scope.gettingData = false;
                    $scope.searchResults = "Please enter a term to search on";
                    $scope.responseStatus = 'error';
                }

            } catch (err) {
                $scope.gettingData = false;
            }
        });

        $(".open-button").on("click", function() {
            $(this).closest('.collapse-group').find('.collapse').collapse('show');
        });

        $(".close-button").on("click", function() {
            $(this).closest('.collapse-group').find('.collapse').collapse('hide');
        });

    }]);]]></script><script_name/><sys_class_name>sys_ui_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-10-18 13:32:18</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>1ee33447db31cb405dbe38f0ad961974</sys_id><sys_mod_count>134</sys_mod_count><sys_name>fc_functions</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ui_script_1ee33447db31cb405dbe38f0ad961974</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2017-11-07 17:32:49</sys_updated_on><use_scoped_format>false</use_scoped_format></sys_ui_script></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.fetchCodeUtils</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>fetchCodeUtils</name><script><![CDATA[var fetchCodeUtils = Class.create();
fetchCodeUtils.prototype = Object.extendsObject(AbstractScriptProcessor, {
    initialize: function() {},

	// global variables
    search: null,
    delimiter: ",",
    resultsObject: {},
    debug: false,
    useAndQuery: true,
    resultFormat: 'both',
    instancePath: "https://" + gs.getProperty('instance_name') + ".service-now.com/",
    fieldName: '',
    additionalFilter: '',

	// Main function
    searchForTerm: function(term, useAndQuery, debug, delimiter, additionalFilter) {
        if (typeof debug != "undefined") this.debug = debug;
        if (typeof delimiter != "undefined") this.delimiter = delimiter;
        if (typeof useAndQuery != "undefined") this.useAndQuery = useAndQuery;
        if (typeof additionalFilter != "undefined") this.additionalFilter = additionalFilter;
        if (typeof term != "string") {
            gs.info("GlobalScriptSearch - ERROR: must pass a valid search term to search");
            return {
                "error": "ERROR: must pass a valid search term to search"
            };
        }
        this.search = term;
        this._searchLocations();
        this._searchFieldTypes();
        this._searchWorkflow();
        return JSON.stringify(this.resultsObject);
    },

	// Searches for specific fields based on table and field name
    _searchLocations: function() {
		
		var locations = JSON.parse(gs.getProperty('fetchcode.specificFieldMapping'));
        for (var location in locations) {
            this._searchLocation(location, locations[location]);
        }
    },

    // Searches for certain types of fields
    _searchFieldTypes: function() {
		
		// Initialize GR for getting fields to search
        var fieldList = new GlideRecord("sys_dictionary");
		
		// Types of fields to search
        var fieldTypes = ["script_plain", "script", "email_script", "condition_string", "conditions"];
		
		// Add all field types to our fieldList query as a addOrQuery
        var addOrQuery = null;
        for (var index_1 = 0; index_1 < fieldTypes.length; index_1++) {
            if (addOrQuery == null)
                addOrQuery = fieldList.addQuery("internal_type", fieldTypes[index_1]);
            else
                addOrQuery.addOrCondition("internal_type", fieldTypes[index_1]);
        }
		
		// Add fields where the element begins or ends with script
        addOrQuery.addOrCondition("element", "ENDSWITH", "script");
        addOrQuery.addOrCondition("element", "STARTSWITH", "script");

        // Exclude all field types that don't come from String
        var nonString = new GlideRecord("sys_glide_object");
        nonString.addQuery("scalar_type", "!=", "string");
        nonString.queryNoDomain();
        while (nonString.next()) {
            fieldList.addQuery("internal_type", "!=", nonString.name + "");
        }
		
		// Exclude Bools
        fieldList.addQuery("internal_type", "!=", "boolean");
		
		// Query for fields to search
        fieldList.queryNoDomain();
        while (fieldList.next()) {
			
			// Exclude fields from tables prefixed with var__
            if (fieldList.name.indexOf("var__") >= 0)
                continue;
			
			// set field name for use in adding matches
            this.fieldName = fieldList.column_label;
			
			// Search for term in this field
            this._searchLocation(fieldList.name, fieldList.element);
        }
    },

    // Searches workflows
    _searchWorkflow: function() {
		
		// The table that workflow activity scripts are stored
        var tableName = 'sys_variable_value';
		
		// the field that houses the scripts
        var fieldName = 'value';
		
        // Initialize GR for searching workflows
        var rec = new GlideRecord(tableName);
		
		// Query for workflow activities
        rec.addQuery('document', 'wf_activity');
		
		// Search for script fields
        var addOrQuery_fieldTypes = rec.addQuery('variable.element', 'CONTAINS', 'script');
        addOrQuery_fieldTypes.addOrCondition('variable.internal_type', 'CONTAINS', 'script');
		
		// Split terms into an array
        var terms = this.search.split(this.delimiter);
		
		// Loop through terms and add them to query
        for (var termsIndex_1 = 0; termsIndex_1 < terms.length; termsIndex_1++) {
			
			// add to query based on if this is an And or an Or query
            if (this.useAndQuery) {
                rec.addQuery(fieldName, 'CONTAINS', terms[termsIndex_1]);
            } else {
				var addOrQuery_terms;
                if (termsIndex_1 == 0)
                    addOrQuery_terms = rec.addQuery(fieldName, "CONTAINS", terms[termsIndex_1]);
                else
                    addOrQuery_terms.addOrCondition(fieldName, "CONTAINS", terms[termsIndex_1]);
            }
        }
		
        // add additional Query
        if (this.additionalFilter)
            rec.addEncodedQuery("^" + this.additionalFilter);
		
		// Check for and add matches if found
        this._addMatches(tableName, fieldName, rec);
    },

    // search for term based on table and field name
    _searchLocation: function(table, field) {
        var fieldName = field + "";
        var tableName = table + "";
		
        if (this.debug)
            gs.info("_searchLocation: " + tableName + " " + fieldName);
		
		// Initialize GR for searching for terms
        var target = new GlideRecord(tableName);
		
		// Check if valid table name
        if (!target.isValid()) {
            gs.info("GlobalScriptSearch - ERRROR: " + tableName + " was an invalid table name (field: " + fieldName + ").");
            return;
        }
		
		// split terms int an array
        var terms = this.search.split(this.delimiter);
		
        if (this.debug)
            gs.info("_searchLocation: terms.length " + terms.length);
		
		// Loop through terms and add them to query
        for (var termsIndex_1 = 0; termsIndex_1 < terms.length; termsIndex_1++) {
			
			// add to query based on if this is an And or an Or query
            if (this.useAndQuery) {
                target.addQuery(fieldName, 'CONTAINS', terms[termsIndex_1]);
            } else {
				var addOrQuery_terms;
                if (termsIndex_1 == 0)
                    addOrQuery_terms = target.addQuery(fieldName, "CONTAINS", terms[termsIndex_1]);
                else
                    addOrQuery_terms.addOrCondition(fieldName, "CONTAINS", terms[termsIndex_1]);
            }
        }
		
        // add additional Query
        if (this.additionalFilter)
            target.addEncodedQuery("^" + this.additionalFilter);

		// Check for and add matches if found
        this._addMatches(tableName, fieldName, target);
    },

    /* Output matching files to the logs. */
    _addMatches: function(tableName, fieldName, match) {
        try {
			
            // Query for matches based on query passed to function
            match.queryNoDomain();
			
            gs.info("fetchCodeUtils: Encoded Query: " + tableName + ":" + match.getEncodedQuery())
			
			// Return if no matches found
            if (match.getRowCount() < 1)
                return;

            // Create table object if it doesnt already exist
            if (!this.resultsObject[tableName]) {
				
                // Get table GlideRecord
                var tableLabel = tableName;
                var targetTable = new GlideRecord('sys_db_object');
                if (targetTable.get('name', tableName)) {
                    tableLabel = targetTable.label.toString();
                }

				// Make label plural if multiple records found
                if (tableLabel.substring(tableLabel.length - 1) != 's') {
					if (tableLabel.substring(tableLabel.length - 1) == 'y') {
						tableLabel = tableLabel.substring(0, tableLabel.length - 1) + 'ies';
					} else {
						tableLabel = tableLabel + 's';
					}
                }
				
                // Create table Object to be passed back to client
                this.resultsObject[tableName] = {
                    tableLabel: tableLabel.toString(),
                    fields: {

                    },
                    recordsMatched: 0,
                    fieldNameList: "",
                    path: this.instancePath + tableName + '_list.do?sysparm_query=sys_idIN'
                };
            }

            // Create field object if it doesnt already exist
            if (!this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName]) {
                this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName] = {
                    matches: {

                    },
                    fieldNameList: "",
                    label: this.fieldName.toString() || fieldName,
                    recordsMatched: 0
                };
            }

            // Add matches to object
            while (match.next()) {

				// Add match data to object
                this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName].matches[match.sys_id] = {
                    name: match.getDisplayValue(),
                    updated_by: match.sys_updated_by.toString(),
                    updated_on: match.sys_updated_on.toString(),
                    created_by: match.sys_created_by.toString(),
                    matchedString: match[fieldName].toString(),
                    table: match.table.toString() || match.collection.toString() || match.model_table.toString() || match.event_name.toString() || match.name.toString(),
                    path: this.instancePath + tableName + ".do?sys_id=" + match.sys_id
                };

				// Split terms into array for use in grabing match snippet
                var terms = this.search.split(this.delimiter);
				
				// Loop through terms and grab first match 
                for (var term in terms) {
                    var subStrFound = false;

                    // Grab snippet of where match was found
                    if (!subStrFound) {
						var endPoint,
							startPoint,
							termLength,
							matchedFieldString = match[fieldName].toString(),
							termToMatch = terms[term],
							termStartPoint = matchedFieldString.indexOf(termToMatch);

						
                        if (termStartPoint != -1) {

                            termLength = terms[term].toString().length;
							
                            if (termStartPoint > 10) {
                                startPoint = termStartPoint - 10;
                            } else {
                                startPoint = 0;
                            }

                            endPoint = termStartPoint + termLength + 10;
							
                            if (parseInt(matchedFieldString.length) > parseInt(endPoint)) {
                            	this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName].matches[match.sys_id].matchSubString = matchedFieldString.substring(parseInt(startPoint), parseInt(endPoint)).toString();
                            } else {
                            	this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName].matches[match.sys_id].matchSubString = matchedFieldString.substring(startPoint).toString();
                            }
                            subStrFound = true;
                        }
                    }
					
					// only return first match
                    if (subStrFound)
                        break;
                }

                // Try to get the table that the records runs on
                if (match.table || match.collection || match.model_table || match.name) {
                    var matchTableName = match.table || match.collection || match.model_table || match.name.split('.')[0];
                    var appliesToTable = new GlideRecord('sys_db_object');
                    if (((appliesToTable.get('name', tableName) || match.sys_class_name == "sys_security_acl") && matchTableName != match.getDisplayValue())) {
                        this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName].showTable = true;
                    }
                    if (match.sys_class_name == "sysevent_script_action") {
                        this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName].showTable = true;
                        this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName].runsOn = "Event";
                    }
                }

                // Get Active state
                if (match.active.toString() == 'true' || match.active.toString() == "false") {
                    this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName].showActive = true;
                    this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName].matches[match.sys_id].isActive = match.active.toString();
                }

                // Add sys_id of match to list of matches
                this.resultsObject[tableName].fieldNameList += match.sys_id.toString() + ",";
                this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName].fieldNameList += match.sys_id.toString() + ",";

                // Count matches
                this.resultsObject[tableName].recordsMatched++;
                this.resultsObject[tableName].fields[fieldName].recordsMatched++;
            }


        } catch (err) {
            gs.info("fetchCodeUtils: ERRROR: failure while trying to insert matches " + err);
        }
    },
    type: 'fetchCodeUtils'
});]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-10-17 13:33:21</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>8cd963e6dbb58b405dbe38f0ad961929</sys_id><sys_mod_count>156</sys_mod_count><sys_name>fetchCodeUtils</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_8cd963e6dbb58b405dbe38f0ad961929</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-03-07 04:31:47</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>
