sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_include_fbd33af6137d1200c794b7a12244b0e3
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.objectify</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description>Script Include to support the Objectify application</description><name>objectify</name><script><![CDATA[var objectify = Class.create();
objectify.prototype = {
	initialize: function() {
		this.debug = gs.getProperty('objectify_debug');
	},

	//Build and return an Object
	//Inputs: identifier(string), inputs(object)
	//Outputs: object
	postObject: function(identifier, input){
		var objectifyObject = {};
		//Check for valid identifier & Object Definition
		var objectDef = this._getObjectDefinition(identifier);
		if (!objectDef.isValidRecord())
			objectifyObject = {
				"objectify_error_code":400,
				"objectify_error":"No Object Definition exists for identifier " + identifier
			};
		else{
			//If object is non-public, check that user is authenticated
			if (objectDef.getValue('public') == false && !gs.isLoggedIn())
				objectifyObject = {
					"objectify_error_code":401,
					"objectify_error":"Unauthenticated access denied for Object with identifier " + identifier
				};
			else{
				//Process input payload and add to objectDef for easier processing
				objectDef.input = this.getInput(identifier, input);
				//Add 'simple' data to Object
				objectifyObject = this._addSimpleData(objectDef, objectifyObject);
				//Add 'smart' data to Object
				objectifyObject = this._addSmartData(objectDef, objectifyObject);
				//Add 'scripted' data to Object
				objectifyObject = this._addScriptedData(objectDef, objectifyObject);
				//Expand object to eliminate any dot-notation
				objectifyObject = this._traverseObject(objectifyObject, this._expandObject);
				//Process magic keys against output, if active magic keys exist
				if (objectDef.getValue('magic_keys') == true && this._areMagicKeys('output'))
					objectifyObject = this._traverseObject(objectifyObject, this._processMagicKeysOutput);
				//Process data transformers against output, if active data transformers exist
				if (objectDef.getValue('data_transformers') == true && this._areDataTransformers('regex'))
					objectifyObject = this._traverseObject(objectifyObject, this._processDataTransformersRegex);
			}
		}
		if (this.debug == 'true')
			gs.info('Objectify: Returning Object generated for identifier "' + objectDef.getValue('identifier') + '": ' + JSON.stringify(objectifyObject));
		return objectifyObject;
	},

	//Build and return the input payload
	//Inputs: objectDef(GlideRecord), input(object)
	//Outputs: object
	getInput: function(identifier, input){
		var processedInput = {};
		//Check for valid identifier & Object Definition
		var objectDef = this._getObjectDefinition(identifier);
		if (!objectDef.isValidRecord())
			processedInput = {"error":"No Object Definition exists for identifier " + identifier};
		else{
			//If input is provided and accepted, use it
			if (this._isValidObject(input) && objectDef.getValue('accepts_input') == true){
				processedInput = input;
				//If retain sample input is true, merge sample input with provided input
				if(objectDef.getValue('retain_sample_input') == true){
					try{
						var sampleInput = eval(objectDef.getValue('request_payload'));
						if (this._isValidObject(sampleInput))
							processedInput = this._mergeObjects(processedInput, sampleInput);
					}
					catch(error){
						if (this.debug == 'true')
							gs.info('Objectify: Error processing sample request payload for object "' + objectDataDef.getValue('key') + '": ' + error);
					}
				}
				if (this.debug == 'true')
					gs.info('Objectify: Input for identifier "' + objectDef.getValue('identifier') + '" received via parameter is ' + JSON.stringify(processedInput));
			}
			//If input is accepted but not provided & retain sample input is true, use sample input from objectDef
			else if (!this._isValidObject(input) && objectDef.getValue('accepts_input') == true && objectDef.getValue('retain_sample_input') == true){
				try{
					processedInput = eval(objectDef.getValue('request_payload'));
				}
				catch(error){
					if (this.debug == 'true')
						gs.info('Objectify: Error processing sample request payload for object "' + objectDataDef.getValue('key') + '": ' + error);
				}
				if (this.debug == 'true')
					gs.info('Objectify: No input for identifier "' + objectDef.getValue('identifier') + '" received via parameter, using sample input ' + JSON.stringify(processedInput));
			}
			else if (!this._isValidObject(input) && objectDef.getValue('accepts_input') == true && objectDef.getValue('retain_sample_input') == false){
				processedInput = {};
				if (this.debug == 'true')
					gs.info('Objectify: Input accepted but none provided for identifier "' + objectDef.getValue('identifier') + '".');
			}
			else if (this.debug == 'true'){
				gs.info('Objectify: No input required or accepted for identifier "' + objectDef.getValue('identifier') + '".');
				return;
			}
			//Process magic keys against input
			if (processedInput && objectDef.getValue('magic_keys') == true && this._areMagicKeys('input')){
				processedInput = this._traverseObject(processedInput, this._processMagicKeysInput);
				if (this.debug == 'true')
					gs.info('Objectify: Processed input (after magic keys) is ' + JSON.stringify(processedInput));
			}
		}
		return processedInput;
	},

	//Add 'simple' data to an existing object
	//Inputs: objectDef(GlideRecord), objectifyObject(object)
	//Outputs: object
	_addSimpleData: function(objectDef, objectifyObject){
		var objectDataDef = new GlideRecord("objectify_data");
		objectDataDef.addQuery("object", objectDef.getValue('sys_id'));
		objectDataDef.addQuery("type", "simple");
		objectDataDef.addQuery("active", true);
		objectDataDef.query();
		while (objectDataDef.next()) {
			//Process dynamic elements inside value, if they exist
			var value = this._getDynamicValue(objectDef.input, objectDataDef.getValue('value'));
			//For each simple data record, build the key value pair
			objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')] = value;
		}
		return objectifyObject;
	},

	//Add 'smart' data to an existing object
	//Inputs: objectDef(GlideRecord), objectifyObject(object)
	//Outputs: object
	_addSmartData: function(objectDef, objectifyObject){
		var objectDataDef = new GlideRecord("objectify_data");
		objectDataDef.addQuery("object", objectDef.getValue('sys_id'));
		objectDataDef.addQuery("type", "smart");
		objectDataDef.addQuery("active", true);
		objectDataDef.query();
		while (objectDataDef.next()) {
			objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')] = {};
			var objectifyObjectArray = [];
			var smartRec;
			var targetRec;
			var recObject;
			//Set query according to secure mode from data definition
			if (objectDataDef.getValue('secure_mode') == true)
				smartRec = new GlideRecordSecure(objectDataDef.getValue('table'));
			else
				smartRec = new GlideRecord(objectDataDef.getValue('table'));
			//Apply dynamically generated query to table
			var encodedQuery;
			encodedQuery = objectDataDef.getValue("condition");
			if (!objectDataDef.condition.nil())
				encodedQuery = this._getDynamicCondition(objectDef.input, objectDataDef.getValue("condition").toString());
			smartRec.addEncodedQuery(encodedQuery);
			//Set total record count & table name in object
			//If overriding target, count deduplicated results
			smartRec.query();
			if (objectDataDef.getValue('override_target') == true){
				var countArray = [];
				while(smartRec.next()){
					recObject = {};
					targetRec = this._getRefFieldRecord(smartRec, objectDataDef.getValue('target'));
					if (targetRec && targetRec.getValue('sys_id')){
						if (!this._isDupeRec(targetRec, countArray)){
							recObject.sys_id = targetRec.getValue('sys_id');
							countArray.push(recObject);
						}
					}
				}
				objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')].total_count = countArray.length;
				objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')].table = objectDataDef.getValue('target_table');
			}
			//If not overriding target, get row count for results
			else{
				objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')].total_count = smartRec.getRowCount();
				objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')].table = objectDataDef.getValue('table');
			}
			//Get max results & set in object
			var maxResults = null;
			if (!objectDataDef.max_results.nil())
				maxResults = parseInt(this._getDynamicValue(objectDef.input, objectDataDef.getValue('max_results')));
			if (!maxResults)
				maxResults = objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')].total_count;
			//Get offset & set in object
			var offset = null;
			if (!objectDataDef.offset.nil())
				offset = parseInt(this._getDynamicValue(objectDef.input, objectDataDef.getValue('offset')));
			if (!offset)
				offset = 0;
			objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')].offset = offset;
			//If not overriding target, apply max results and offset to query explicitly
			if (objectDataDef.getValue('override_target') == false){
				//If offset exists, apply window to results for target table
				if (offset > 0)
					smartRec.chooseWindow(offset, offset+maxResults);
				//Else apply maximum results limit for target table
				else if (maxResults < objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')].total_count){
					smartRec.setLimit(maxResults);
				}
			}
			if (this.debug == 'true')
				gs.info('Objectify: Applying encoded query "' + encodedQuery + '" to table "' + objectDataDef.getValue('table') + '" w/ offset ' + offset + ' and max results ' + maxResults + ' for data definition with key "' + objectDataDef.getValue('key') + '" and Object identifier "' + objectDef.getValue('identifier') + '".');
			smartRec.query();
			while (smartRec.next()) {
				recObject = {};
				//Set (and optionally override) target record
				targetRec = smartRec;
				if (objectDataDef.getValue('override_target') == true)
					targetRec = this._getRefFieldRecord(smartRec, objectDataDef.getValue('target'));
				if (targetRec && targetRec.getValue('sys_id')){
					//If new record is not a duplicate, add to the array
					if (!this._isDupeRec(targetRec, objectifyObjectArray)){
						recObject.sys_id = targetRec.getValue('sys_id');
						//Add any additional fields specified for the target record to the object
						recObject = this._addFields(recObject, objectDef, objectDataDef, targetRec);
						objectifyObjectArray.push(recObject);
						//If overriding target, we can stop gathering as soon as sufficient results are obtained
						if (objectDataDef.getValue('override_target') == true && objectifyObjectArray.length >= (maxResults + offset))
							break;
					}
				}
				else if (this.debug == 'true')
					gs.info('Objectify: There is no valid target record for ' + smartRec.getDisplayValue() + '. Ignoring.');
			}
			//If overriding target, manually slice array down to correct offset & maxResults
			if (objectDataDef.getValue('override_target') == true)
				objectifyObjectArray = objectifyObjectArray.slice(offset, maxResults + offset);
			//Add return object array to the return object
			if (objectifyObjectArray.length > 0)
				objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')].records = objectifyObjectArray;
			else
				objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')].records = [];
			objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')].returned_count = objectifyObjectArray.length;
		}
		return objectifyObject;
	},

	//Add 'scripted' data to an existing object
	//Inputs: objectDef(GlideRecord), objectifyObject(object)
	//Outputs: object
	_addScriptedData: function(objectDef, objectifyObject){
		var objectDataDef = new GlideRecord("objectify_data");
		objectDataDef.addQuery("object", objectDef.getValue('sys_id'));
		objectDataDef.addQuery("type", "scripted");
		objectDataDef.addQuery("active", true);
		objectDataDef.orderBy("order");
		objectDataDef.query();
		while (objectDataDef.next()) {
			//Add input object and attempt to eval script
			//If successful, build the key value pair. If not, throw error
			try{
				var input = objectDef.input;
				objectifyObject[objectDataDef.getValue('key')] = eval(objectDataDef.getValue('script'));
			}
			catch(error){
				if (this.debug == 'true'){
					gs.info('Objectify: Error processing scripted data definition with key "' + objectDataDef.getValue('key') + '" and Object identifier ' + objectDef.getValue('identifier') + ': ' + error);
				}
			}
		}
		return objectifyObject;
	},

	//Add data to Smart Data object from fields field
	//Inputs: recObject(object), objectDef(GlideRecord), objectDataDef(GlideRecord), targetRec(GlideRecord)
	//Outputs: object
	_addFields: function(recObject, objectDef, objectDataDef, targetRec){
		//Get basic fields from Smart data record
		if (!objectDataDef.fields.nil()){
			var fieldsArray = objectDataDef.getValue('fields').toString().split(',');
			//Iterate through fields array and add key:value pairs
			for (var i=0; i < fieldsArray.length; i++){
				var fieldElement = targetRec.getElement(fieldsArray[i]);
				var fieldType = fieldElement.getED().getInternalType();
				//If field is a reference field, force it to key of 'sys_id'.
				//This avoids overwrites when a ref field is gathered along with dot-walks on that field.
				if (fieldType == 'reference')
					fieldsArray[i] += '.sys_id';
				//Process field value via Data Transformers
				if (objectDef.getValue('data_transformers') == true)
					recObject[fieldsArray[i]] = this._processDataTransformersDataType(fieldElement);
				else{
					var fieldValue = fieldElement.toString();
					//Use display value if no field value exists (for photos, etc)
					if (!fieldValue || fieldType.indexOf('image') > -1)
						fieldValue = fieldElement.getDisplayValue();
					recObject[fieldsArray[i]] = fieldValue;
				}
			}
		}
		//Get Additional Link Fields records for scripted fields
		recObject = this._addAdditionalData(recObject, objectDef, objectDataDef, targetRec);
		return recObject;
	},

	///Add data to Smart Data object from additional fields records
	//Inputs: recObject(object), objectDef(GlideRecord), objectDataDef(GlideRecord), targetRec(GlideRecord)
	//Outputs: object
	_addAdditionalData: function(recObject, objectDef, objectDataDef, targetRec){
		var additionalData = new GlideRecord("objectify_additional_data");
		additionalData.addQuery("object_data", objectDataDef.getValue("sys_id"));
		additionalData.addQuery("active", true);
		additionalData.query();
		while (additionalData.next()) {
			var input = objectDef.input;
			var record = targetRec;
			//For each additional data record on this target, gather and add to object
			if (additionalData.type == 'simple'){
				//Process dynamic elements inside value
				var value = this._getDynamicValue(objectDef.input, additionalData.getValue('value'), record);
				//For each simple data record, build the key value pair
				recObject[additionalData.getValue('key')] = value;
			}
			else if (additionalData.type == 'scripted'){
				try{
					recObject[additionalData.getValue('key')] = eval(additionalData.getValue('script'));
				}
				catch(error){
					if (this.debug == 'true')
						gs.info('Objectify: Error processing scripted additional data definition with key "' + additionalData.getValue('key') + '", Data Definition identifier ' + objectDataDef.getValue('identifier') + ', and Object identifier ' + objectDef.getValue('identifier') + ': ' + error);
				}
			}
		}
		return recObject;
	},

	//Route input object Magic Keys
	//Inputs: o(object)
	//Outputs: object
	_processMagicKeysInput: function(o){
		var obj = o;
		//Iterate through Magic Key records, looking for matches and working magic
		var magicKeyRec = new GlideRecord("objectify_magic_key");
		magicKeyRec.addQuery("active", true);
		magicKeyRec.addQuery("type", "input");
		magicKeyRec.query();
		while (magicKeyRec.next()) {
			obj = this._processMagicKeys(obj, magicKeyRec);
		}
		return obj;
	},
	//Route output object Magic Keys
	//Inputs: o(object)
	//Outputs: object
	_processMagicKeysOutput: function(o){
		var obj = o;
		//Iterate through Magic Key records, looking for matches and working magic
		var magicKeyRec = new GlideRecord("objectify_magic_key");
		magicKeyRec.addQuery("active", true);
		magicKeyRec.addQuery("type", "output");
		magicKeyRec.query();
		while (magicKeyRec.next()) {
			obj = this._processMagicKeys(obj, magicKeyRec);
		}
		return obj;
	},
	//Enhance an object w/ magic keys, replacing key combinations with richer data
	//Inputs: obj(object), magicKeyRec(GlideRecord)
	//Outputs: object
	_processMagicKeys: function(obj, magicKeyRec){
		var magicKeysArray = magicKeyRec.getValue('keys').toString().replace(/ /g,'').split(',');
		var match = true;
		for (var i = 0; i < magicKeysArray.length; i++) {
			if (!(magicKeysArray[i] in obj)){
				match = false;
				break;
			}
		}
		if (match){
			try{
				var magicObject = eval(magicKeyRec.getValue('script'));
				if (typeof magicObject === 'object'){
					if (this.debug == 'true')
						gs.info('Objectify: Magic key "' + magicKeyRec.getValue('name') + '" matched object ' + JSON.stringify(obj) + ' and concatenated ' + JSON.stringify(magicObject));
					obj = this._mergeObjects(obj, magicObject);
				}
			}
			catch(error){
				if (this.debug == 'true')
					gs.info('Objectify: Error processing scripted Magic Key "' + magicKeyRec.getValue('name') + '" with ' + magicKeyRec.getValue('type') + ' object ' + JSON.stringify(obj) + ': ' + error);
			}
		}
		return obj;
	},

	//Transform output data with Data Transformers (from data type)
	//Inputs: element(GlideElement)
	//Outputs: string
	_processDataTransformersDataType: function(element){
		var elementType = element.getED().getInternalType();
		var value = element.toString();
		//Use display value if no field value exists (for photos, etc)
		if (!value || elementType.indexOf('image') > -1)
			value = element.getDisplayValue();
		var dataTransRec = new GlideRecord("objectify_data_transformer");
		dataTransRec.addQuery("active", true);
		dataTransRec.addQuery("type", "data_type");
		dataTransRec.addQuery("data_type.name", elementType);
		dataTransRec.query();
		if (dataTransRec.next()) {
			try{
				var newValue = eval(dataTransRec.getValue('script'));
				if (this.debug == 'true')
					gs.info('Objectify: Data Transformer "' + dataTransRec.getValue('name') + '" matched value "' + value + '"(' + typeof value + ') from data type and replaced it with "' + newValue + '"(' + typeof newValue + ').');
				return newValue;
			}
			catch(error){
				if (this.debug == 'true')
					gs.info('Objectify: Error processing scripted Data Transformer(data type) "' + dataTransRec.getValue('name') + '" with input element ' + element.toString() + ': ' + error);
			}
		}
		return value;
	},
	//Transform output data with Data Transformers (from regex)
	//Inputs: o(object)
	//Outputs: object
	_processDataTransformersRegex: function(o){
		var oo = o;
		var dataTransRec = new GlideRecord("objectify_data_transformer");
		dataTransRec.addQuery("active", true);
		dataTransRec.addQuery("type", "regex");
		dataTransRec.query();
		while (dataTransRec.next()) {
			try{
				for (var key in oo){
					var value = oo[key];
					if (typeof value === 'string'){
						var regx = dataTransRec.getValue('regex');
						if (this._isRegexMatch(value, regx)){
							oo[key] = eval(dataTransRec.getValue('script'));
							if (this.debug == 'true')
								gs.info('Objectify: Data Transformer "' + dataTransRec.getValue('name') + '" matched value "' + value + '"(' + typeof value + ') from regex and replaced it with "' + oo[key] + '"(' + typeof oo[key] + ').');
						}
					}
				}
			}
			catch(error){
				if (this.debug == 'true')
					gs.info('Objectify: Error processing scripted Data Transformer(regex) "' + dataTransRec.getValue('name') + '" with input object ' + JSON.stringify(o) + ': ' + error);
			}
		}
		return oo;
	},

	//Get an Object Definition
	//Inputs: identifier(string)
	//Outputs: GlideRecord
	_getObjectDefinition: function(identifier){
		var objectDef = new GlideRecord("objectify_object");
		objectDef.addQuery("identifier", identifier);
		objectDef.addQuery("active", true);
		objectDef.query();
		if (objectDef.next())
			return objectDef;
		return;
	},

	//Get the table associated with a reference field on table
	//Inputs: table(string), field(string)
	//Outputs: string
	_getRefFieldTable: function(table, field){
		var tempRec = new GlideRecord(table);
		tempRec.initialize();
		var tableName = this._getRefFieldRecord(tempRec, field).getTableName();
		return tableName;
	},

	//Get the record associated with a dot-walked reference field on table
	//Inputs: record(GlideRecord), field(string)
	//Outputs: GlideRecord
	_getRefFieldRecord: function(record, field){
		return record.getElement(field).getRefRecord();
	},

	//Evaluate and replace javascript & dynamic filter conditions in an encodedQuery
	//Inputs: input(object), valueString(string), record(GlideRecord - optional)
	//Outputs: string
	//*Perhaps replace w/ GlideFilter.checkRecord() in future?
	_getDynamicCondition: function(input, valueString, record){
		//Split ^ for primary value elements
		var fieldValueArraySplit1 = valueString.split('EQ')[0].split('^');
    	for (var i = 0; i < fieldValueArraySplit1.length; i++){
    		//Split @ for compound value elements
    		var fieldValueArraySplit2 = fieldValueArraySplit1[i].split('@');
    		//Iterate through elements to evaluate dynamic content
    		for (var j= 0; j < fieldValueArraySplit2.length; j++){
	    		var fieldNameOperator;
	    		var fieldValue;
	    		//Process javascript evals
	    		if (fieldValueArraySplit2[j].indexOf('javascript:') > -1){
	    			//Break value element into name/operator and value pairs
	    			//Then, assess value and rebuild value element
					fieldNameOperator = fieldValueArraySplit2[j].split('javascript:')[0];
					fieldValue = fieldValueArraySplit2[j].split('javascript:')[1];
					try{
						newFieldValue = eval(fieldValue);
						valueString = valueString.replace(fieldValueArraySplit2[j], fieldNameOperator + newFieldValue);
						if (this.debug == 'true')
							gs.info('Objectify: Replaced javascript condition "' + fieldValueArraySplit2[j] + '" with "' + fieldNameOperator + newFieldValue + '".');
					}
					catch(e){
						if (this.debug == 'true')
							gs.info('Objectify: Error processing javascript for value string ' + valueString + ': ' + e);
					}
	    		}
	    		//Process dynamic filter options
	    		if (fieldValueArraySplit2[j].indexOf('DYNAMIC') > -1){
	    			//Break value element into name/operator and value pairs
	    			//Then, assess value and rebuild value element
					fieldNameOperator = fieldValueArraySplit2[j].split('DYNAMIC')[0];
					fieldValue = fieldValueArraySplit2[j].split('DYNAMIC')[1];
					try{
						newFieldValue = eval(this._getDynamicFilter(fieldValue).getValue('script'));
						valueString = valueString.replace(fieldValueArraySplit2[j], fieldNameOperator + newFieldValue);
						if (this.debug == 'true')
							gs.info('Objectify: Replaced dynamic filter condition "' + fieldValueArraySplit2[j] + '" with "' + fieldNameOperator + newFieldValue + '".');
					}
					catch(e){
						if (this.debug == 'true')
							gs.info('Objectify: Error processing dynamic filter for condition string ' + valueString + ': ' + e);
					}
	    		}
	    	}
    	}
    	return valueString;
	},

	//Get dynamic value from a javascript: prepended string
	//Inputs: input(object), value(string), record(GlideRecord - optional)
	//Outputs: string/object/array
	_getDynamicValue: function(input, value, record){
		var origValue = value;
		if (value.indexOf('javascript:') == 0){
			try{
				value = eval(value.substring(11));
				if (this.debug == 'true')
					gs.info('Objectify: Replaced dynamic value "' + origValue + '" with "' + JSON.stringify(value) + '".');
			}
			catch(e){
				if (this.debug == 'true')
					gs.info('Objectify: Error processing dynamic value for value string ' + value + ': ' + e);
			}
		}
		return value;
	},

	//Get a dynamic filter option
	//Inputs: filterID(string)
	//Outputs: GlideRecord
	_getDynamicFilter: function(filterID){
		var dynamicFilter = new GlideRecord("sys_filter_option_dynamic");
		if (dynamicFilter.get(filterID))
			return dynamicFilter;
		return;
	},

	//Check if a record already exists in an object array (to eliminate dupes)
	//Inputs: record(GlideRecord), objectArray(array)
	//Outputs: boolean
	_isDupeRec: function(record, objectArray){
		//Check if record is already found in object
		var objectArrayString = JSON.stringify(objectArray);
		if (objectArrayString.indexOf(record.getValue('sys_id')) > -1)
			return true;
		return false;
	},

	//Check if a string value matches against a regular expression
	//Inputs: value(string), regx(string)
	//Outputs: boolean
	_isRegexMatch: function(value, regx){
		var re = new RegExp(regx);
		if (re.test(value))
			return true;
		return false;
	},

	//Check if active Magic Keys exist of a certain type
	//Inputs: type(string)
	//Outputs: boolean
	_areMagicKeys: function(type){
		var count = new GlideAggregate('objectify_magic_key');
		count.addQuery('active', true);
		count.addQuery('type', type);
		count.addAggregate('COUNT');
		count.query();
		if (count.next() && count.getAggregate('COUNT') > 0)
		   return true;
		return false;
	},

	//Check if active Data Transformers exist
	//Inputs: type(string)
	//Outputs: boolean
	_areDataTransformers: function(type){
		var count = new GlideAggregate('objectify_data_transformer');
		count.addQuery('active', true);
		count.addQuery('type', type);
		count.addAggregate('COUNT');
		count.query();
		if (count.next() && count.getAggregate('COUNT') > 0)
		   return true;
		return false;
	},

	//Traverse all objects/arrays in a hierarchy and apply a function to each
	//Inputs: o(object), func(function name)
	//Outputs: none
	_traverseObject: function(o, func) {
		for (var i in o) {
			if (o[i] !== null && typeof(o[i])=="object")
				o[i] = this._traverseObject(o[i],func);
		}
		o = func.apply(this,[o]);
		return o;
	},

	//Expand an object based on dot-notation used in keys
	//Inputs: o(object or array)
	//Outputs: object
	_expandObject: function(o) {
		var oo, t, parts, part;
		//Check object to ensure we maintain array/object constructor
		if (o.constructor === Array)
			oo = [];
		else
			oo = {};
		for (var k in o) {
			t = oo;
			parts = k.split('.');
			var key = parts.pop();
			while (parts.length) {
		  		part = parts.shift();
		  		t = t[part] = t[part] || {};
		  		/*
				//Playing with the idea of merging identically named objects instead of enforcing uniqueness
		  		if (!t[part] && (!o[part] || (typeof o[part] !== 'object')))
		  			t[part] = {};
		  		else if (o[part] && typeof o[part] === 'object'){
		  			t[part] = this._mergeObjects(o[part],t[part]);
		  		}
		  		t = t[part];*/
			}
			t[key] = o[k];
		}
		return oo;
	},

	//Merge two objects
	//Input: obj1(object), obj2(object)
	//Output: object
	_mergeObjects: function(obj1, obj2){
		for (var k in obj2){
			//Only merge if key doesn't exist in target
			if (!(k in obj1))
				obj1[k] = obj2[k];
		}
		return obj1;
	},

	//Check if an input is a valid, non-empty object
	//Input: obj(object)
	//Output: boolean
	_isValidObject: function(obj){
		if (obj && typeof obj === 'object'){
			for(var key in obj) {
				if(obj.hasOwnProperty(key))
					return true;
			}
		}
		return false;
	},

	type: 'objectify'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-02-29 15:39:50</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>fbd33af6137d1200c794b7a12244b0e3</sys_id><sys_mod_count>509</sys_mod_count><sys_name>objectify</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_fbd33af6137d1200c794b7a12244b0e3</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>ben.hollifield@snc_SHARE</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2016-06-10 12:06:16</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>
